**__{{Site-333 -- Interdepartmental Text-Based Communications Log:}}__**
{{25/12/2023 -- 11:33 am (EDT)}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[cell]]
* ##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##, Director;
* ##red|**Tony Catalano**##, Accounting & Tourism;
* ##green|**Leonora Morales**##, Wildlife Specialist;
* ##orange|**Noah Patel**##, Cryptozoologist & Museum Curator.
[[/cell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[cell]]
##red|**Tony Catalano:**## Happy Holidays, everyone! 

##orange|**Noah Patel:**## Merry Christmas!

##green|**Leonora Morales:**## Thanks again for cooking dinner, Vincent. 

##blue|**Vincent Bohart:**## Don't expect me to make a habit out of it. 

##red|**Tony Catalano:**## As strange as it feels to write this, I kind of actually.... had a good time?

##green|**Leonora Morales:**## Yeah, me too. Well, I suppose we can avoid writing you up for misuse of the Foundation emergent breach channels, Vincent. It is the holidays, after all. 

##blue|**Vincent Bohart:**## I don't appreciate the slander. 

##green|**Leonora Morales:**## Slander is written, this is libel. I'm using speech-to-text.

##blue|**Vincent Bohart:**## You're liable to be getting a disciplinary report for insubordination. 

##red|**Tony Catalano:**## There's the Scrooge we know. 

##orange|**Noah Patel:**## Have any of you felt kind of off the last few days? I have and I'm wondering if it has to do with what we ate.

##red|**Tony Catalano:**## Maybe a little bloated. 

##green|**Leonora Morales:**## What //did// we eat? 

##blue|**Vincent Bohart:**## Oh yeah, I figured out what was going on there. 

##green|**Leonora Morales:**## You're just telling us this now?

##orange|**Noah Patel:**## Was I right it was a turducken? 

##blue|**Vincent Bohart:**## Gas leak. 

##red|**Tony Catalano:**## What?

##blue|**Vincent Bohart:**## //Major// gas leak. Like off the charts, the oven was free-pouring it into the site. 

##red|**Tony Catalano:**## One-day-old Christ. Seriously?

##blue|**Vincent Bohart:**## That's not even the half of it. It turns out everything on site: the oven, the boiler, the furnace, the hot tub, everything that heats up, is powered by burning sewer gas. We had an agreement with a group calling themselves the '[*https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-7715 Plumbers],' which saved us a lot in heating costs. 

##blue|**Vincent Bohart:**## This isn't natural gas, it's //natural// gas, and chances are it's been leaking for a few weeks now. The whole Site is like a dry Christmas tree in a chimney. 

##green|**Leonora Morales:**## Thank god we stopped Noah from flaming the pudding when he burned himself. 

##red|**Tony Catalano:**## Or that the damn [*https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-8472-ex rat didn't set it off].

##blue|**Vincent Bohart:**## Yeah, so any way that's the reason for the season. 

##green|**Leonora Morales:**## So how are we just now learning about this?

##blue|**Vincent Bohart:**## Oh. One of those interns must have messed around with the monoxide detector or something when they triggered that breach alarm. 

##red|**Tony Catalano:**## That doesn't explain anything. 

##blue|**Vincent Bohart:**## Mysteries of life. Anyway, they need some time to fix the oven and pump all the gas out of the old building. 

##blue|**Vincent Bohart:**## So I suppose you're all getting an extra week of vacation. Happy Holidays. As for me...
-----
= {{##blue|**Vincent Bohart:**## Has set out of office reply: **On the way to Vegas. See you in the New Year.**}}
